<subSubSection id="E923C0B0288E9A1313FC34661EEBED37" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0B8A94F7ACC81E23F30E8A12EE9760B0" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="33F0B5DB4D23F1B46EBFEF8D8C4E4ECA" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">
Pileus dark violet to dark brown, whitish context; hymenophore pink-purple to violet-brown; stipe surface tomentose to longitudinally fribrillose; basidiospores 9-13 
<normalizedToken id="06B5122FD22B694BB80B0B0F6D44F44B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4-5 
<normalizedToken id="3630DCB3E9758CE3098A95107475C160" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, surface with cylindrical pits; pleurocystidia and cheilocystidia fusiform-ventricose to lanceolate.
</paragraph>
<caption id="261636589819BA87E47BE09B87B51F0C" doi="10.3897/mycokeys.88.73951.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/665983" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" start="Figure 6" startId="F6">
