</taxonomicName>
by a white hymenium when young, becoming pinkish to pale cocoa at maturity; stipe clavate, surface dry, coarsely reticulated on the upper two- thirds, reticulated, finely tomentose; basidiospores 13-19 
<normalizedToken id="C657D01D2BD149062DE2622DCB8DA80C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5-8 
<normalizedToken id="6C12A6CD21B9DEB7739FB2A3E4BBDEDA" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, smooth to rugose-punctate, ovoid-elliptical, narrowly ovoid, inequilateral profile.
